After digging a bit into the implementation of the component, the theme prop responsible for the chevron color is onSurfaceVariant. So I did this in my component:

```
const accordionTheme = useMemo(
    () => ({
      ...theme,
      colors: {
        ...theme.colors,
        onSurfaceVariant: theme.colors.secondary,
      },
    }),
    [theme],
  );
```

And on the component:

```
 <List.Accordion
          theme={accordionTheme}
          {... all your other stuff} />
```
